        "text": "Because our transactions can take weeks or months to complete, we obviously run our\nsimulations faster than real time using a simulated clock. The visualizer post-processes the\nresults of the simulation to produce an overview two dimensional picture of the progression of\nthe transaction through time, using a page format inspired by the \"swim lane diagrams\" made\npopular in business process reengineering. The overview contains a\ncolumn of each person involved in the transaction and icons with fly-out details representing\nimportant interactions. This format has worked well for our need, but could easily be substituted\nwith some other format without invalidating the rest of our results or even modification of the\ntest scripts."
